# Intervention Effects


::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

:::


## Fatphobia


::: {.cell}

:::


Fatphobia was assessed at the three time points for both BAM (N = 26) and Body Project (N = 24) participants using the Goldfarb Fear of Fat Scale [@goldfarbGoldfarbFearFat1985].

Within the BAM group, the effect sizes for GFFS were as follows:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.51, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.35, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.16, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

Within the Body Project group, the effect sizes for GFFS were as follows:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.61, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.6, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.01, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

## Anti-fat Bias


::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

:::


Anti-fat Bias was also assessed at all three time points using the Universal Measure of Bias-FAT (UMB-FAT)[@dursoUnderstandingSelfdirectedStigma2008] and the Eating Pathology Symptoms Inventory (EPSI) negative attitudes toward obesity subcale [@coniglioFactorialIntegrityValidation2018].

Within the BAM group, the effect sizes for UMB-FAT were as follows:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.59, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.25, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.33, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

Within the Body Project group, the effect sizes for UMB-FAT were as follows:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.24, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.06, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.14, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

## Thin Ideal Internalization


::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

:::


Furthermore, thin ideal internalization was assessed using the Sociocultural Attitudes Towards Appearance Questionnaire (SATAQ) [@schaeferDevelopmentValidationSociocultural2015] and the Ideal Body Stereotype Scale - Revised (IBSS-R) [@sticeTestDualPathway1996].

Within the BAM group, the effect sizes for SATAQ were as follows:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.47, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.18, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.27, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

Within the Body Project group, the effect sizes for SATAQ were as follows:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.41, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.12, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.24, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

Furthermore, the effect sizes for the IBSS-R for the BAM group were:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.82, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.47, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.2, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

Within the Body Project group, the effect sizes for IBSS-R were as follows:

-   The effect size between baseline and post-session was -0.52, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between baseline and 8 weeks was -0.47, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].

-   The effect size between post-session and 8 weeks was 0.02, indicating \[interpretation of effect size\].
